Text: I am trying to extract a jar file from matlab code using javac builder. I have set as environment variable JAVA_HOME: `C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.7.0_71` and in PATH variable `C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.7.0_71\\bin`. When I am write in console `java -version ` I am getting `java version 1.8.0_20` while when I am running `javac -version` I am getting `1.7.0_71`. It seems that matlab could no find javac variable, thus, I am not able to compile my ,m code into .jar file. What should I check in order to put correctly the link of Matlab and correct java version?

I am trying to extract a jar file from matlab code using javac builder. 

I have set as environment variable `JAVA_HOME`: 

`C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.7.0_71` 

and in `PATH` variable: 

`C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.7.0_71\\bin`. 

When I am write in console `java -version `, I am getting `java version 1.8.0_20` while when I am running `javac -version` I am getting `1.7.0_71`. 

It seems that matlab could no find javac variable, thus, I am not able to compile my `.m` code into `.jar` file.

What should I check in order to put correctly the link of Matlab and correct java version?

I am trying to extract a jar file from matlab code using javac builder. 

I have set as environment variable `JAVA_HOME`: 

`C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_20` 

and in `PATH` variable: 

`C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_20\\bin`. 

When I am write in console `java -version `, I am getting `java version 1.8.0_20` while when I am running `javac -version` I am getting `jdk1.8.0_20`. 

However, it seems that matlab could no find javac variable, thus, I am not able to compile my `.m` code into `.jar` file. When I tried to compile .m code I got the following:

    Error: An error occurred while shelling out to javac (error code = -1).
    Unable to build executable.
    Executing command: ""C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_20;\\bin\\javac" 

Where should I check for the following error: `C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_20\\bin;\\bin\\javac`?
What should I check in order to put correctly the link of Matlab and correct java version?
